ices and Other Related Offences Commission, ICPC, for demanding and allegedly receiving N500,000, bribe from an accused person facing trial in his court. July 31, 2011 In "News" An Ogun State High Court sitting in Isabo, Abeokuta has discharged and acquitted the immediate past Vice Chancellor of Federal University of Agriculture, Abeokuta (FUNAAB), Professor Olusola Oyewole in the suit filed by the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission. May 17, 2018 In "News" ABUJA—Chairman of Zenon Petroleum and Gas Ltd., Chief Femi Otedola, yesterday, told an Abuja High Court sitting at Apo that it was the Department of State Services, DSS, that gave him the $500,000 bribe money he offered to erstwhile Chairman of the House of Representatives Ad Hoc Committee on Fuel… January 29, 2019 In "Crime Guard"